The article discusses the bilateral relations between the United States and Belgium. It highlights the strong bonds of friendship and cooperation that have existed since 1832. The two countries have fought side by side in wars and have supported each other in times of need. Belgium is a valued NATO ally and hosts the NATO Headquarters. It has also contributed to NATO operations and other international missions. The United States and Belgium work together to promote security, human rights, and prosperity. They cooperate on counterterrorism efforts and have economic and commercial ties. The article also mentions the negotiation of the Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership (T-TIP) as an opportunity to further strengthen the economic relationship between the two countries. Additionally, educational and cultural programs contribute to the partnership between Belgian and U.S. universities.